{"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Topics","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Notes-on-Conversion","doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/ThrowingPropertyWrapper","doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/_Concurrency\/Task"]},{"title":"Functions","anchor":"Functions","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/zip(_:)"]},{"title":"Extended Modules","anchor":"Extended-Modules","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Swift"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"Thrappture","symbolKind":"module","title":"Thrappture","role":"collection","roleHeading":"Framework","modules":[{"name":"Thrappture"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"Treat ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"text":" like the throwing property wrappers they are.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/thrappture"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Property wrappers cannot throw."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"text":" are not property wrappers.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This package imagines what life would be like if those statements were not true. 🤩","type":"text"}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"What’s a “Throwing Property Wrapper”?","anchor":"Whats-a-Throwing-Property-Wrapper"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some types are conceptually just wrappers around a value, giving it additional behavior. Swift uses ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/properties\/#Property-Wrappers","type":"reference"},{"text":" to represent these types.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"But while throwing errors from properties is supported, throwing errors from a property wrapper’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wrappedValue"},{"type":"text","text":" property, specifically, is not (yet). That’s what a “throwing property wrapper” would employ."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Optional and Result should be throwing property wrappers.","anchor":"Optional-and-Result-should-be-throwing-property-wrappers"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" both predate property wrappers, but it’s the right model for them, and we should embrace that as much as possible."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While we can’t actually "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"turn them"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" into throwing property wrappers, thinking of them that way enables aids with understanding the helpful utilities found in this package."}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Optional","anchor":"Optional"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" acts ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"halfway"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" to being a property wrapper.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"set"}]}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" an optional to what would be its “","type":"text"},{"code":"\"wrappedValue","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"”.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["var value: Optional = 1","value = 2"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"But there is no mechanism in place to assign an optional to an instance of its wrapped value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let newValue: Int = value \/\/ Value of optional type 'Int?' must be unwrapped to a value of type 'Int'"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"And it’s as if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" somehow had an overloaded "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wrappedValue"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"set"},{"type":"text","text":" accessor to match that, because you can also "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"set"}]}]},{"type":"text","text":" an optional to be another optional."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["value = .some(3)","value = nil"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Property wrappers deal with that kind of conflation by using ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"projected values"}]},{"text":", by way of “","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$"},{"text":"” syntax. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"text":" were a throwing property wrapper, the syntax would be this, instead:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Optional var value = 1","value = 2","$value = .some(3)","$value = nil","let newValue: Int = try value"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"What would that last line throw? "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Swift\/Optional\/Nil","overridingTitle":"Optional.Nil","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Optional.Nil"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"text":"Result","anchor":"Result","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"text":" doesn’t have the conflation problem that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"text":" does, but that’s because it doesn’t offer any syntactic sugar.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" were a throwing property wrapper, the syntax for a “"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" version” of the previous example would be this:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@Result<_, Int?.Nil> var value = 1","value = 2","$value = .success(3)","$value = .failure(nil)","let newValue: Int = try value"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"level":3,"text":"Usage Examples","anchor":"Usage-Examples","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You’ve got the source code, so aside from reading this documentation, see the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Tests"}]},{"text":" folder for example usage! 😺","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Treat ","type":"text"},{"code":"Optional","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" like the throwing property wrappers they are.","type":"text"}],"title":"Thrappture","role":"collection","type":"topic"},"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/Swift":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture\/swift","type":"topic","abstract":[],"role":"collection","title":"Swift","identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Swift"},"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/Swift/Optional/Nil":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Swift\/Optional\/Nil","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture\/swift\/optional\/nil","title":"Optional.Nil","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Nil","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Nil","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An error that represents that an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Optional"},{"type":"text","text":" was "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/zip(_:)":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"zip","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"<each ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Sequence","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(repeat each ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Sequence","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Sequence","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<(repeat (each ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Sequence","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":").","kind":"text"},{"text":"Element","preciseIdentifier":"s:ST7ElementQa","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")>\n","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/zip(_:)","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture\/zip(_:)","type":"topic","title":"zip(_:)"},"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/Notes-on-Conversion":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/Notes-on-Conversion","title":"Notes on Conversion","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture\/notes-on-conversion","abstract":[]},"https://docs.swift.org/swift-book/documentation/the-swift-programming-language/properties/#Property-Wrappers":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"property wrappers"}],"url":"https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/properties\/#Property-Wrappers","title":"property wrappers","identifier":"https:\/\/docs.swift.org\/swift-book\/documentation\/the-swift-programming-language\/properties\/#Property-Wrappers","type":"link"},"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/_Concurrency/Task":{"fragments":[{"text":"extension","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Task","kind":"identifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScT"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Task","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/_Concurrency\/Task","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Explicit specializations for more generic overloads."}],"title":"Task","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture\/_concurrency\/task","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://Thrappture/documentation/Thrappture/ThrowingPropertyWrapper":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThrowingPropertyWrapper"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A type that could be a property wrapper if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"get throws"},{"type":"text","text":" were supported for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"wrappedValue"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThrowingPropertyWrapper"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Thrappture\/documentation\/Thrappture\/ThrowingPropertyWrapper","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/thrappture\/throwingpropertywrapper","role":"symbol","title":"ThrowingPropertyWrapper"}}}